<TITLE> BDR arrests 8 including 6 Indians </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sylhet May 9 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh Rifles arrested eight persons including six Indians from the Jaintapur border. They were arrested on Sunday afternoon from Sripur area of the border. 20 set of dresses resembling military uniform, around Rs 22,000, six mobile sets, 10 Indian SIM cards and two Bangladeshi mobile SIM cards were recovered from them. But the BDR did not inform whether the dresses looked like the uniform of the Indian armed forces. Second in command of 21 Rifles Battalion Maj Abdullah Al Mamun told the journalists that the six Indian Manipuris were arrested at 4:10 from the Sripur area when they were trespassing into Bangladesh. The two Bangladeshi accompanying them were also arrested. Process of handing them over to the Jaintapur police is under way, said the BDR official. bdnews24
